<subSubSection lastPageId="20" lastPageNumber="21" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="19.[151,1437,1114,2011]" lastBlockId="20.[151,1436,153,252]" lastPageId="20" lastPageNumber="21" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,335,1948,1975]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Comments.</emphasis>
This species is promptly recognized by having the head wider than long; the mandible with three very small teeth; the notaulus complete; the mesoscutum-mesoscutellar suture strongly arched, deep and wide; the hypopygeal posterior margin concave and the genitalia with the apical dorsal projection of the basiparamere very large.
</paragraph>
